  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Numbers 18:19",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:19",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "A covenant of salt — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A durable and perpetual covenant; so called here, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 13:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", either because salt is of singular use to preserve things from corruption, and was an emblem of friendship; or because it was ratified on their part by salt, which is therefore called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the salt of the covenant, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for which the priests were obliged to take care that it should never be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "lacking from any meal-offering, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 2:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". And this privilege conferred upon the priests is called a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "covenant, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because it was given them conditionally, upon condition of their service and care about the worship of God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
