  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "All the heave offerings of the holy things,.... All before mentioned, and whatsoever comes under that name: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which the children of Israel offer unto the Lord; either by his commandment, or of their own freewill: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "have I given thee, and thy sons, and thy daughters with thee, by a statute for ever: so providing for their maintenance by an irrepealable law as long as their priesthood lasted, even until the Messiah should come: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "it is a covenant of salt for ever before the Lord unto thee, and thy seed with thee: an incorruptible, inviolable, durable covenant, which should last for ever, even until the Gospel dispensation or world to come should take place; and it would remain ever before the Lord in his sight, who would take care it should never be made void, but stand fast with Aaron and his posterity as long as his priesthood endured. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "it is a covenant of salt for ever before the Lord unto thee, and thy seed with thee: an incorruptible, inviolable, durable covenant, which should last for ever, even until the Gospel dispensation or world to come should take place; and it would remain ever before the Lord in his sight, who would take care it should never be made void, but stand fast with Aaron and his posterity as long as his priesthood endured. ",
